{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a124", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 163, "line_end": 163, "parent_section": "§4.1.8.1 [Origin Metadata for Variables]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "#### 4.1.8.1 Origin Metadata for Variables", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 1, "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a125", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 165, "line_end": 165, "parent_section": "§4.1.8.1 [Origin Metadata for Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The origin element in the Define-XML file is used to indicate where the data originated.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a126", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 165, "line_end": 165, "parent_section": "§4.1.8.1 [Origin Metadata for Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Its purpose is to unambiguously communicate to the reviewer the origin of the data source.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a127", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 165, "line_end": 165, "parent_section": "§4.1.8.1 [Origin Metadata for Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For example, data could be collected (on the CRF, from a vendor, or from a device), derived, or assigned; CRF data should be traceable to an annotated CRF and derived data should be traceable to some derivation algorithm.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a128", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 165, "line_end": 165, "parent_section": "§4.1.8.1 [Origin Metadata for Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The Define-XML specification is the definitive source of allowable origin values.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a129", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 165, "line_end": 165, "parent_section": "§4.1.8.1 [Origin Metadata for Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Additional guidance and supporting examples can be referenced using the Metadata Submission Guidelines (MSG) for SDTMIG.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a130", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 167, "line_end": 167, "parent_section": "§4.1.8.2 [Origin Metadata for Records]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "#### 4.1.8.2 Origin Metadata for Records", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 2, "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a131", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 169, "line_end": 169, "parent_section": "§4.1.8.2 [Origin Metadata for Records]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Sponsors are cautioned to recognize that a derived origin means that all values for that variable were derived, and that collected on the CRF applies to all values as well.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a132", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 169, "line_end": 169, "parent_section": "§4.1.8.2 [Origin Metadata for Records]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In some cases, both collected and derived values may be reported in the same field.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a133", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 169, "line_end": 169, "parent_section": "§4.1.8.2 [Origin Metadata for Records]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For example, some records in a Findings dataset such as Questionnaires (QS) contain values collected from the CRF; other records may contain derived values, such as a total score.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a134", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 169, "line_end": 169, "parent_section": "§4.1.8.2 [Origin Metadata for Records]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "When both derived and collected values are reported in a variable, the origin is to be described using value-level metadata in the Define-XML document.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a135", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 171, "line_end": 171, "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "### 4.1.9 Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 9, "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a136", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 173, "line_end": 173, "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Section 3.2, Using the CDISC Domain Models in Regulatory Submissions — Dataset Metadata, indicates that a sponsor should include in the metadata the variables that contribute to the natural key for a domain.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a137", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 173, "line_end": 173, "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In a case where a dataset includes a mix of records with different natural keys, the natural key that provides the most granularity is the one that should be provided.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a138", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 173, "line_end": 173, "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The following example illustrates how to do this, and include a case where a Supplemental Qualifier variable is referenced because it forms part of the natural key.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a139", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 175, "line_end": 175, "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "**Musculoskeletal System Findings (MK) Domain Example**", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a140", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 177, "line_end": 177, "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Sponsor A chooses the following natural key for the MK domain:", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a141", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 179, "line_end": 179, "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "CODE_LITERAL", "verbatim": "STUDYID, USUBJID, VISITNUM, MKTESTCD", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a142", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 181, "line_end": 181, "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Sponsor B collects data in such a way that the location (MKLOC and MKLAT) and method (MKMETHOD) variables need to be included in the natural key to identify a unique row.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a143", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 181, "line_end": 181, "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Sponsor B then defines the following natural key for the MK domain:", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a144", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 183, "line_end": 183, "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "CODE_LITERAL", "verbatim": "STUDYID, USUBJID, VISITNUM, MKTESTCD, MKLOC, MKLAT, MKMETHOD", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a145", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 185, "line_end": 185, "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In certain instances a Supplemental Qualifier variable (i.e., a QNAM value; see Section 8.4, Relating Non-standard Variable Values to a Parent Domain) might also contribute to the natural key of a record, and therefore needs to be referenced as part of the natural key for a domain.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a146", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 185, "line_end": 185, "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The important concept here is that a domain is not limited by physical structure.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a147", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 185, "line_end": 185, "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "A domain may comprise more than 1 physical dataset (e.g., the main domain dataset and its associated Supplemental Qualifiers dataset).", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a148", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 185, "line_end": 185, "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Supplemental Qualifier variables should be referenced in the natural key by using a 2-part name.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a149", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 185, "line_end": 185, "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The word QNAM must be used as the first part of the name to indicate that the contributing variable exists in a domain-specific SUPP--; the second part is the value of QNAM that ultimately becomes a column reference when the SUPPQUAL records are joined on to the main domain dataset (e.g., QNAM.XVAR when the SUPP-- record has a QNAM of \"XVAR\").", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a150", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 187, "line_end": 187, "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In this example, sponsor B might have collected data that used different imaging methods, using imaging devices with different makes and models, and using different hand positions.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a151", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 187, "line_end": 187, "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The sponsor considers the make and model information and hand position to be essential data that contributes to the uniqueness of the test result, and so includes a device identifier (SPDEVID) in the data and creates a Supplemental Qualifier variable for hand position (QNAM = \"MKHNDPOS\").", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a152", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 187, "line_end": 187, "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The natural key is then defined as follows:", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a153", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 189, "line_end": 190, "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "CODE_LITERAL", "verbatim": "    STUDYID, USUBJID, SPDEVID, VISITNUM, MKTESTCD, MKLOC, MKLAT, MKMETHOD,\n    QNAM.MKHNDPOS", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a154", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 192, "line_end": 192, "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "where the notation \"QNAM.MKHNDPOS\" means the Supplemental Qualifier whose QNAM is \"MKHNDPOS\".", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a155", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 192, "line_end": 192, "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This approach becomes very useful in a Findings domain when --TESTCD values are \"generic\" and rely on other variables to completely describe the test.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a156", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 192, "line_end": 192, "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The use of generic test codes helps to create distinct lists of manageable controlled terminology for --TESTCD.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a157", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 192, "line_end": 192, "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In studies where multiple repetitive tests or measurements are being made, for example in a rheumatoid arthritis study where repetitive measurements of bone erosion in the hands and wrists might be made using both X-ray and MRI equipment, the generic MKTEST \"Sharp/Genari Bone Erosion Score\" would be used in combination with other variables to fully identify the result.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_ch04_a158", "file": "chapters/ch04_general_assumptions.md", "line_start": 194, "line_end": 194, "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Taking just the phalanges, a sponsor might want to express the following in a test in order to make it unique:", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
